accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The collection is open to all researchers. However, files from the Document Records Series requires prior review from the University Archivist to determine if there is a need to restrict access to any, or all records, in the file in accordance to the Archives' restriction policy concerning personnel records.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The materials in this collection may be protected by copyright law (U.S. Code: Title 17). Any use of the material which exceeds fair use requires permission from the copyright holder. Researchers are solely responsible for obtaining the proper permission(s) for their use of the material.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The information on each individual has come from a variety of sources at the Hartt School. Most of the material came from the offices of the Directors and Deans of Hartt. Other material has come from publicity files, and some compositions appear to have been transferred from the Hartt College/Allen Library.

In 2015, the call number was changed from HM25 to ARCH063.Reprocessed by Tiffany Crawford, 2016; Amanda Talbot, 2017; and Joseph Spence, 2018 and 2019. In 2018, the collection was reprocessed and the photographs in the collection were separated from documents and moved into their own series. In 2019, music compositions were added to the online finding aid, and additional compositions were added to the collection.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains material related to the activities of administrators and faculty of the Hartt School. These materials include programs, correspondence, writings, compositions, newspaper clippings, photographs, and faculty data.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged into four series: I. Document records, II. Photographs, III. Compositions, and IV. Duplicates.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Files from the Document Records Series requires prior review from the University Archivist to determine if there is a need to restrict access to any, or all records, in the file in accordance to the Archives' restriction policy concerning personnel records.
